-- Rousseff Keeps Her Lead Over Serra in Brazil Vox Populi Poll, Folha Says
-- Maria Luiza Rabello
-- 2010-06-29T19:23:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/rousseff-keeps-her-lead-over-serra-in-brazil-vox-populi-poll-folha-says.html

          
          
             Brazilian presidential candidate
 Dilma Rousseff  maintained her lead over former Sao Paulo
Governor  Jose Serra  before the country’s October elections,
according to Vox Populi poll, Folha de S. Paulo columnist
 Fernando Rodrigues  reported on the newspaper’s  website .  
 Rousseff, former Cabinet chief to President  Luiz Inacio Lula  da Silva, is supported by 40 percent of those surveyed, the
report said. Opposition Social Democracy Party candidate Serra
had 35 percent support, the newspaper said.  
 The nationwide poll of 3,000 people was taken June 24 to
June 26 and has a margin of error of 1.8 percentage points,
Folha reported.  
